 :tx/rationale "Create task: ST-1: Auto-detect session start and write session-start datoms. BACKGROUND: When the CLI detects no active session (no :session/current entity, or existing one has started-at > 2 hours old), auto-start a new session as a side-effect of the first meaningful command. This is the same pattern as ZCM-1 (auto-observe). APPROACH: (1) Add detect_or_start_session(store, layout, agent) function — checks for :session/current, validates freshness, creates session entity if needed. (2) Session entity has: :session/started-at (wall_time), :session/start-fitness (F(S) at start), :session/start-datom-count, :session/start-task-closed-count, :session/start-spec-coverage, :session/start-methodology (M(t) at start), :session/agent, :session/current true. (3) Call from maybe_inject_footer or main.rs post-dispatch (runs after every command). (4) Schema: add 6 new :session/* attributes. ACCEPTANCE: (A) First braid command in fresh session creates session entity. (B) Subsequent commands reuse existing session. (C) Session older than 2h is auto-closed and new one started. (D) :session/start-fitness matches F(S) at creation time. TESTS: (1) Unit: fresh store → session created. (2) Unit: existing session → no new session. (3) Unit: stale session (>2h) → new session. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs + crates/braid/src/main.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs. TRACES TO: INV-HARVEST-001, INV-BILATERAL-001."
